(436, 26, 'page lead', 'Operating a local governmental unit always has challenges and opportunities. You may be looking for new efficiencies, projecting changes in tax revenue, finding new revenue sources, working on long-range planning, funding buildings and improvements, or structuring the most advantageous economic development package. Our years of experience in helping others in similar situations make us uniquely qualified to help you today -- and with tomorrow''s challenges.'),
