(133, 1, '2010-12-14 12:38:52', '2010-12-14 12:38:52', 'Daniel A. Hedden''s practice is focused on management advisory  services, ranging from training to budget services, budget modeling,  financial management reports and advanced services involving financial  accounting and reporting. In addition, he assists governmental units  with process management and increasing their technology utilization to  provide better and more useful information to a wider range of users.  Hedden has been involved with financial studies for municipally-owned  utilities, not-for-profit corporations, regional water and sewer  districts and conservancy districts.\r\n\r\nHedden joined Umbaugh in 1996 and became a principal in the Accounting Services Group in 2007.\r\n\r\nHe served in the United States  Army and the Indiana Army National Guard and is a graduate of Indiana  University-Purdue University in Indianapolis with degrees in accounting  and finance. He has completed professional courses sponsored by the  American Institute of Certified Public Accountants, the Indiana CPA  Society and other professional organizations. Hedden is a member of the  American Institute of Certified Public Accountants, the Indiana CPA  Society, the Association of Government Accountants and the American  Water Works Association.\r\n\r\nHedden lives in Fortville and is based in Umbaugh''s Indianapolis office.', 'Daniel A. Hedden', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'daniel-a-hedden', '', '', '2010-12-21 13:40:43', '2010-12-21 13:40:43', '', 0, 'http://localhost/umbaugh/?post_type=partner&p=133', 0, 'partner', '', 0),
